['When you visit our website, we store cookies on your browser to collect information. The information collected might relate to you, your preferences or your device, and is mostly used to make the site work as you expect it to and to provide a more personalized web experience. 

Under the California Consumer Privacy Act of 2018 ("CCPA"), California residents have the right to opt out of the "sale" of personal information (transfers or disclosures to other businesses or third parties for monetary or other valuable consideration) we collect about them ("Personal Data") as described in our Privacy & Cookies Policy.  You can find our Privacy & Cookies Policy by clicking on the link below.

We value your privacy and want to honor your preferences regarding your data. Guidelines from the State of California setting forth exactly how companies are required to comply with CCPA are still being developed, and we will monitor those developments carefully. Set forth below are options for California residents who want to opt-out of certain transfers of data that we may have collected from you as you have interacted with our website, our apps, or otherwise used our services. We may update this information as guidance from the State of California is clarified and finalized.

Generally, transfers of data occur (1) because of cookies and similar technologies on your desktop browser or your mobile device, or (2) from our systems.  To exercise your choice with respect to cookies or other technologies, please use the button below.  To let us know about your choices with respect to other transfers, please submit a DSAR request using the link below.
